quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  51,43,"And in Thamûd (there is also a sign), when they were told: "
  51,44,"But they insolently defied the Command of their Lord, so the Sâ‘iqah{1} overtook them while they were looking.",1:[{51:44} Sâ‘iqah: A destructive awful cry, torment, hit, a thunderbolt, See (Verse 41:13).]
  51,45,"Then they were unable to rise up, nor could they help themselves."
  52,34,"Let them then produce a recital like unto it (the Qur’ân) if they are truthful."
  52,35,"Were they created by nothing? Or were they themselves the creators?"
  52,36,"Or did they create the heavens and the earth? Nay, but they have no firm Belief."
  53,28,"But they have no knowledge thereof. They follow but a guess, and verily, guess is no substitute for the truth."
  53,29,"Therefore withdraw (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) from him who turns away from Our Reminder (this Qur’ân) and desires nothing but the life of this world."
  53,30,"That is what they could reach of knowledge. Verily, your Lord it is He Who knows best him who goes astray from His Path, and He knows best him who receives guidance."
  54,19,"Verily, We sent against them a furious wind of harsh voice on a day of evil omen and continuous calamity."
  54,20,"Plucking out men as if they were uprooted stems of date-palms."
  54,21,"Then, how (terrible) was My Torment and My Warnings?"
  55,13,"Then which of the Blessings of your Lord will you both (jinn and men) deny?"
  55,14,"He created man (Adam) from sounding clay like the clay of pottery."
  55,15,"And the jinn: He created from a smokeless flame of fire."
  56,4,"When the earth will be shaken with a terrible shake."
  56,5,"And the mountains will be powdered to dust,"
  56,6,"So that they will become floating dust particles."